

ABOUT
-----
Reg2Rep provides simple mechanism allowing you to register and un-register
objects in centralized repository. It uses Amazon AWS SimpleDB by default.

COPYRIGHT AND LICENSE
---------------------

Copyright (c) 2010 VanillaDesk Ltd. http://www.vanilladesk.com

See file LICENSE for details on license.

HOW TO INSTALL
--------------

Simple - run install.sh

Install script will 
 a) download necessary archive from github reg2rep downloads
 b) install reg2rep in /usr/local/lib
 c) create example configuration file in /etc/reg2rep/example.conf
 d) create init.d start/stop script
 g) register init.d script in rc.d so MongoDB is started automatically

HOW TO USE
----------

Follow documentation in MongoDB wiki http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Home.